The cuts did not stop at health. The administration moved to shut down USAID, a congressionally created agency, by folding its functions into the State Department. Voice of America saw its funding cut. The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, which had just proposed rules that would touch technology companies including Musk\'92s X, found itself targeted by DOGE. Social Security field offices were slated for closure until protests forced a partial retreat, even as new ID and Social Security number policies threatened to flood those same offices with hundreds of thousands of extra visitors each week. FEMA, facing what meteorologists warned could be a generational flooding event in Kentucky and across the central United States, was placed under a hiring freeze. The message to the civil service was blunt. Neutral capacity, especially in agencies that regulate markets, protect consumers, or inform the public, was expendable. Loyalty and private influence were not.\
